The paper discusses research publications and their citation distributions, which are common topics in computer science sub-fields such as digital libraries (cs.DL), social networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of power law and lognormal distributions is also common in these sub-fields.
